    <note>Xie(1) Shufang [13270] One guesses that he was a Chenliu Xie(1), but according to Zhou Jiayou, 1.130 ff., there were no Xie(1) zaixiang in Tang and therefore the descendants of the Chenliu Xie(1) could not be traced. Since both Zhou(1) Bida and Yang(2) Wanli's funerary inscriptions for Xie(1) E [13279] provide information about ancestry and migration that is completely independent of Zhou Jiayou and XTS, but with partial confirmation in Renming Da cidian, p. 1677 (without move), this adds to the evidence for the continuity of genealogies held by many lineages. See also descendant Xie(1) E's documentation.</note>
